---
import Section from '../Section.astro';
import { demos } from '../../data/demos';
import { testimonial } from '../../data/home';
import { LayoutGrid, ArrowRight } from '@lucide/astro';
---
<Section id="tools">
  {/* Header built inline, not via SectionHead — the accent on "supply chain"
      needs markup in the title (SectionHead takes a plain string; its own doc
      says richer titles build inline).

      This absorbs the old Moat section. Moat stated the supply-chain moat and
      then showed three tools; LiveTools showed all seven again on the same page.
      The claim was worth keeping, the second listing was not.

      The home page is a WELCOME and a NAVIGATION HUB. It states the moat and opens
      the door; it does not try to be the gallery. The live Production Plan Churn
      console used to be embedded right here — 600px of dense operational tooling
      dropped into the middle of a pitch, which read as plopped-in. The tools are the
      hero of this business, but /work/ is where they're the hero of the page. */}
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <p class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
      <span class="section-index">/ 02</span>
      <span class="mono-label">The moat · supply chain</span>
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">
      Where I go deepest: <span class="aiq-accent">supply chain</span>.
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-muted">
      The whole operation — the flow of material and the systems that run it, across planning,
      sourcing, production, logistics, warehousing, engineering and quality. I’ve run the parts
      most software is built without ever touching, so the problem is understood in operational
      terms, not a spec, before a line of code exists.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-muted">
      These aren’t case studies. They’re the actual tools — running in your browser on synthetic
      data, no login, nothing to install. Open one and start clicking.
    </p>
  </div>

  {/* One doorway. The tools are not re-listed here — /work/ already presents them
      properly (screenshots, blurbs, grouped as a supply-chain map), and a home page
      that re-lists them worse is just the gallery, twice. */}
  <a
    href="/work/"
    class="panel group lift lift-cyan spotlight mt-8 flex items-center gap-4 border-accent/40 p-5"
  >
    <span class="grid h-11 w-11 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-lg border border-line bg-canvas text-cyan">
      <LayoutGrid size={20} aria-hidden="true" />
    </span>
    <span class="min-w-0 flex-1">
      <span class="mono-label text-cyan-deep">All {demos.length} live tools</span>
      <span class="mt-0.5 block font-display font-semibold text-ink">
        Open the full gallery — grouped as a supply-chain map.
      </span>
    </span>
    <ArrowRight
      size={18}
      class="shrink-0 text-cyan transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5"
      aria-hidden="true"
    />
  </a>

  {testimonial && (
    <figure class="mt-10 max-w-3xl">
      <blockquote class="pullquote">{testimonial.quote}</blockquote>
      <figcaption class="mono-label mt-4">
        {testimonial.attribution}{testimonial.role ? ` · ${testimonial.role}` : ''}
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  )}
  {/* SLOT: first real, consented client testimonial drops in via `testimonial` in data/home.ts. */}
</Section>
